@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"
@{fg shine}Introduction@{fg text}

Supershapes uses the @{"Superformula" System "Multiview Superformula.iff"} to create organic shapes.
The "Superformula" was discovered by the biologist Johan Gielis.

It allows to create a almost infinite number of different shapes
by only changing a some parameter values.

Additional information about Johan Gielis and his superformula
can be found at @{"http://www.geniaal.be" System "OpenURL http://www.geniaal.be"}.

@endnode
@node COPYRIGHTNOTICE "Copyright notice"
@{fg shine}Copyright notice@{fg text}

Supershapes was written by @{"Norman Walter" link THEAUTHOR}.

It's freely distributable as long as no changes are made.

@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"
@{fg shine}Requirements@{fg text}

Supershapes works with any Amiga computer with at least
AmigaOS 3.0 and iff.datatype.

@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"
@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

You can control the parameter values by playing arround with the
sliders or by entering a value into the input fields.

If "immediate" is activated, the graphic will update in realtime.
Otherwise click on the "apply" button to redraw the graphic.

@endnode

@node SAVINGGRAPHICS "Saving graphics"
@{fg shine}Saving graphics@{fg text}

You can save your shapes in two different file formats:
IFF-ILBM and EPS (Encapsulated Post Script).

Choose "Save Iff" or "Save EPS" from the pulldown menu.
Then enter the filename into the file requester.

Use IFF-ILBM for bitmap paint programms like "Personal Paint"
or "Art Effect".

EPS is a vector file format. This means, that you can scale
the graphic without quality loss. Use it together with
programms like "WordWorth" or "Page Stream".

@endnode
